    "summary": "I have a keen interest in transforming food systems into ones that can thrive within environmental and social boundaries. Food systems that provide nutritious food to keep us healthy, that develop diverse markets to improve farmers' livelihoods and make healthy foods accessible for everyone, while at the same time protect and promote ecosystem health. \nI believe that systemic approaches will allow us to overcome the environmental and social challenges we face. Transitions towards sustainable food systems can only be achieved if we have a clear overview of all actors and sectors involved, their interactions, and a thorough understanding of the factors influencing them. I am convinced that every stakeholder involved in an issue has important insights to share, and that collaboration is key to produce innovative solutions. \nFinally, I am happy to work together with colleagues from all academic and cultural backgrounds!\n\nmarcia.arredondorivera@gmail.com\nFood systems transformation \u2502 Interdisciplinarity\u2502 Governance\u2502 Sustainable development",
